        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Personal Computer (PC)'); ?>
        <p>A <strong>Personal Computer</strong> (<strong>PC</strong>) is a general purpose computer, whose size, capabilities and original sale price makes it useful for individuals, and which is intended to be operated directly by an end user with no intervening computer operator.</p>
        <p>This contrasted with the batch processing or time sharing models which allowed larger, more expensive minicomputer and mainframe systems to be used by many people, usually at the same time.</p>
        <p>Software applications for most personal computers include, but are not limited to, word processing, spreadsheets, databases, Web browsers and e-mail clients, digital media playback, games and myriad personal productivity and special purpose software applications.</p>
        <p>Modern personal computers often have connections to the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Internet', 'ITN'); ?>, allowing access to the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('World Wide Web', 'WD'); ?> and a wide range of other resources.</p>
        <p>Personal computers may be connected to a local area network (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('LAN', 'ITN'); ?>), either by a cable or a wireless connection.</p>
